10/04/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The country's new defence minister, Teodor Melescanu, visited some of the 605 the Romanian troops serving with the international coalition in Iraq on Monday (April 9th). Aides described it as a fact-finding mission, aimed at getting acquainted with the situation on the ground, the Romanians' duties and their collaboration with foreign partners. Melescanu took over the ministry post last week, after a government shuffle. (Rompres, Mediafax - 09/04/07)
